      • createProtoMessageBuilder

        public static java.lang.Object createProtoMessageBuilder(java.lang.Class clazz,
                                                         java.lang.Object domainObject)
                                                  throws java.lang.NoSuchMethodException,
                                                         java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException,
                                                         java.lang.IllegalAccessException
        Creates a protobuf object builder based on the class passed in with all the variables of the domainObject. It should also work for non protobuf generated classes as long as they have a builder and follow the same naming convention.

        eg. if the domainObject has a variable: long objectId the proto class should have long objectId_ as well as a builder with: newBuilder() and setObjectId(long value) methods. See `package com.kaitait.testFixtures.proto` for an example.

        Parameters:
        clazz - the class of the object builder returned
        domainObject - the object to convert
        Returns:
        a builder instance of the type clazz
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException
        java.lang.NoSuchMethodException
        java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException
